		<!-- message -->
		<div>This is just a summary of all the suggestions on what might be a fair exchange for having one of our two major abilities (porting) given away bit by bit to the entire playerbase until we are no longer needed (for this function) <br />
<br />
It's not a demand for ALL of these to be implemented. It's a list of ideas for SOE to look over and pick one or two out, that might give wizards some group utility.<br />
<br />
And why is it ok to give away pretty much an entire line of our spells (druids' too) but not ok to request a spell that is similar to CotH? It's not as if thats the only thing mages do...we aren't demading the ability to summon all sorts of things like pet toys, focus items, etc, it's just an idea for a spell that fits in with out porting ability.  (See, Mages summon THINGS out of thin air...you'd think summoning people they might accidentally scramble their insides, or something....I've always thought since wizards transport LIVE beings, CotH should have been a wizard ability, but that's just my opinion. And Mages can keep CotH, really <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" /> )<br />
<br />
Or why is it not ok to ask for a magical means to open locks, when it can be justified under the same rationalization that it is &quot;poor game mechanics&quot; to prevent people's access to content just because a certain class (rogues/bards) is not available.  (Just turning SOE's reasoning back on them for a change...what's good for the goose is good for the gander, and all that.)<br />
<br />
Anyhow, spells to suppress mobs gating and/or summoning, would be my preference.  Or a lot more convenience ports &amp; TLs (that are OURS and won't be given away.)  And,  please oh powers-that-be: targettable improved Invis, so we can help the clerics survive the trip to teh GoD trials, hehehe...</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
